Body:
Description: SG_LocalAdmins scan is not picking up changes for some users we identified were disabled and are still showing as active on the SA_SG_LocalAdmins_Details table.
Even if we reduce the scan's scope to just a few servers those users were on, the scan keeps showing "2025-03-19 06:00:00" as the Date Audited with stale data. 
Please Advise
Invitation updated. Attendees: No attendees listed
Invitation updated. Attendees: Joshua Sexton, Alan A. Moreno

zoom meeting (11:30AM EST)

sent reminder email at 11:48AM EST

client joined at 11:15AM EST

 

NEA 11.3.0.138

 

user has been removed from local admin groups but still shows in reports

the date audited correctly reflect when the user was removed from those groups

 

should the Windows Local admin group be purging removed users?

Steps to Reproduce Updated: 1. Run LocalAdmins job
2. Observe more than 1 audit date in the _Details table
What We've Learned Updated: The workflow has been customized by ProServ
Next Steps Updated: Review custom job. Customer is collecting debug logs next time the job runs.
Invitation updated. Attendees: Tay Caliguiri, Alan A. Moreno, Clayton Bridges

What We've Learned Updated: The workflow has been customized by ProServ.

I renamed the old _details table to preserve the old data while we troubleshoot. Then we ran the job against one of the smaller hosts to successfully rebuild the _Details table.

Now we've configure the job to run against all the windows hosts again to narrow down which hosts are having issues currently, who is no longer active, etc.
Next Steps Updated: Wait for the job to complete and have a follow-up meeting to correct host errors (where are we missing perms and ports?)
Invitation updated. Attendees: Tay Caliguiri, Alan A. Moreno
